<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-196-274 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 541 774</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  March 25 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for Mac: $497 LC displays from Mirror. (Mirror TechnologiesInc.'s Pixelview I and Pixelview II monitors) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mirror Technologies Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    MIRR.andO;Product:   Mirror Technologies PixelView II (Monitor, monochrome) (Productintroduction)Mirror Technologies PixelView I (Monitor, monochrome) (Productintroduction)Apple Macintosh LC (Microcomputer) (Equipment and supplies).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMonitorsMonochrome.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR MAC: $497 LC Displays From Mirror 03/25/91 ROSEVILLE, MINNESOTA,U.S.A., 1991 MAR 25 (NB) -- Mirror Technologies is now shipping two largescreen displays for the Macintosh LC.andP;  The new monitors start at $497 for the15-inch Pixelview I full page display, with a screen resolution of 640 by 870and 80 dots per-inch (dpi).andM;The dual page Pixelview II 19-inch model, with a resolution of 1024 X 768 and72 dpi has a suggested list price of $897.andP;  Pixelview II offers WYSIWYG (WhatYou See Is What You Get, computerize for saying the screen display is exactlywhat the printed product will look like) display.andP;  Both models come with aninternal video board.andP;  The power drain is less than 190 milliamps andaccording to Mirror Technologies will not create any problem for the LC'ssmall power supply.andP;  Included is Mirror's Desktop Designer software utilitywhich includes pop-up menus, an enlarged cursor and menu bar, screen saverand screen copy.andM;Thomas Burke, VP of sales and marketing for Mirror Technologies, says,&quot;Mirror was the first to ship a large screen display for the Mac Classic, andwe're extremely proud of our development for doing it again with the LCsolution.&quot; Burke said sales forecasts indicate that more than 650,000 LCswill be sold in 1991, providing a strong market for the new large screendisplays.andM;Mirror Technologies sells directly to the customer, and has reduced the priceof the Pixelview I by $100.andP;  A 24-hour toll free order hotline, 30-day moneyback policy and overnight delivery are available.andP;  The company can be reachedat 800-654-5294.andP;  In January 1991, Mirror Technologies released threePixelview large screen monochrome displays for the IBM and compatiblesmarket.andP;  Those units are priced from $997 to $1797.andM;(Jim Mallory/19910324/Press Contact: Thomas Burke, Mirror Technologies,415-377-0478 or 800-654-5294)</TEXT></DOC>